## Resource Management

**Claude 4.5 Sonnet Model Limits (November 2025):**

- Maximum concurrent: 5 instances per orchestrator
- Typical usage: 3-5 for complex reasoning
- Resource overhead: ~500MB RAM per instance
- Processing time: 60-120 seconds per task (deep analysis)
- Release: October 2024

**Performance Characteristics:**

- Complex reasoning: 60-120 seconds
- Architectural design: 90-150 seconds
- Strategic planning: 60-90 seconds
- Deep code analysis: 120-300 seconds
- 5 parallel Sonnet: ~5x faster than sequential

**When to Use Claude 4.5 Sonnet:**

- Complex architectural decisions
- Multi-file refactoring analysis
- Security-critical code review
- High cyclomatic complexity (>15)
- Deep integration synthesis
- Strategic planning and design
- Quality-critical analysis

**Cost Considerations:**

- Claude 4.5 Sonnet is expensive - use strategically
- Reserve for complex reasoning and strategic work only
- Use Codex/Haiku/Gemini for simple/fast tasks
- Maximize value per Sonnet instance

